                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="34"><font size="2" face="Verdana">I'll
                        try to summarise what was decided at the meeting and
                        where I can, give the reasoning behind it.</font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="21"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="216"><font face="Verdana" size="2">We
                        as a guild will be aiming to complete the Thurgadin
                        Quest Armour. This means killing giants. The reasons
                        behind this are 1) It's the easier of the 3 quest armour
                        sets. 2) You don't need high faction to complete the
                        quest 3) Any change in faction is reversible. 4) You
                        don't need 6 groups to kill Giants in the arena. 5) We
                        already have the numbers to do these quests. 6) We can
                        also do the Coldain Ring and Shawl quests.</font>
                        <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Once we have completed
                        the armour and misc. quests we want to do, we will then
                        be changing faction to Giant. By this time our members
                        will have the items and armour to be able to take down
                        the higher end mobs from Temple of Veeshan, etc, and at
                        the same time had the experience of fighting in Kael.</font></p>
                        <p><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b>Please Note:</b> We
                        are not forcing anyone to pick the same SoV faction as
                        us, we will simply be directing Guild efforts down this
                        path.</font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="21"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="74"><font size="2" face="Verdana">As
                        a direct result of the decision on the SoV Faction we
                        will be implementing an ELP or Event Lottery System.
                        This will hopefully ensure that those that put the
                        effort in, receive the greater reward.</font>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana"><b>To that end the
                        general system will be as follows :-</b></font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="21"><font size="2" face="Verdana">Initial
                        ELP's will be set at 2 ELP's for every level above 45th.
                        So a level 60 will start with 30 ELP's.&nbsp; As of the
                        2nd July 2001 these numbers will be set, so make sure
                        your character level is up to date by this time. </font>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">Every time a member
                        attains a new level past 45th he/she is awarded 2 ELP's.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">Each participant of an
                        Official Raid will be awarded 2 ELP's.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">Participants arriving
                        more than 30 minutes late for the Official Start Time
                        will only be awarded 1 ELP.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">An Official Raid is
                        designated by there being more than 3 or more groups
                        there OR if a Guild Councillor officially calls it a
                        Raid.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana"><b>The System of
                        Lottery will be as follows :-</b></font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="21"><font size="2" face="Verdana">When
                        an Item drops that you can use AND is an upgrade OR is
                        part of a quest, you send a tell to the person in charge
                        of Lotto's with the number of ELP's you wish to bid.
                        There is a 2 minute limit after which time bids are
                        closed.</font>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">If bids are tied then
                        the tied bidders are put into a set lotto i.e. Player#A
                        is 1, Player#B is 2, then /random 1 2.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">If a bid is won by an
                        excessive amount, a 5 point deduction is made i.e.
                        someone bids 20 points and the next highest bid was 2.
                        Then the winner only pays 15 = 20 - 5.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">If NO ONE bids on the
                        item and the Item is NO DROP, then those that can use
                        the item are put into a set lotto as described above.</font></p>
                        <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">If NO ONE bids and the
                        item is tradeable, the item is lottoed to all those
                        present.</font></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td width="100%" height="11" align="center"><font size="2" face="Verdana"><b>NOTE:
                        Please Rules Are Subject to Change at ANY Time.</b></font></td>
                    </tr>
